The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Spouse nabbed
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Spouse nabbed
                            
	Rourkela: One Brundaban Kishan was arrested on Friday for allegedly gouging out an eye and breaking at least seven teeth of his wife, Tulsi Kishan, after the latter failed to meet a dowry demand at Gopinathpur Ghosra village under Bonai police station.         
	The victim filed her complaint with the police on Thursday after undergoing extensive treatment.         
	Son kills man        
	Rourkela: A manhunt was started on Friday to nab the man who killed his 50-year-old father for behaving abnormally with his family and neighbours at Ladadega village under Talsara police station, 150km from here. Amarish Kujur (35), the son of Emil Kujur, allegedly killed his father late on Thursday night.         
	Train mishap        
	Biharsharif: A person was killed and four others were injured when a train crashed into a tractor at an unmanned level crossing in Bihars Nalanda district on Friday. The 2233UP Rajgir-Danapur Passenger rammed into a tractor-trolley at the crossing near Kondupur village under Deepnagar police station, killing one person and injuring four.         
	The deceased was identified as the tractor driver, Babloo Chaudhary. All the four wounded were travelling in the tractor-trolley. The injured have been admitted to the Sadar hospital where their condition was reported to be serious.                                                                                                                                                                         
